src/axiom-website/download.html Windows 10 install instructions

Goal: Axiom Maintenance


Axiom can now run on Windows 10, including Hyperdoc:

(in windows)
<a href="https://www.ghacks.net/2015/06/13/how-to-enable-developer-mode-in-windows-10-to-sideload-apps/">enable developer mode</a>

(in windows) run powershell as admin and type:
Enable-WindowsOptionalFeatures -Online -FeatureName Microsoft-Windows-Subsystem-Linux

(in windows) visit Windows store and download Ubuntu

(in windows) run Ubuntu to install it

(in windows) download the axiom Ubuntu64 <a href="downloads/axiom-ubuntu64-may2017-bin.tgz">binary</a>
http://axiom-developer.org/axiom-website/downloads/axiom-ubuntu64-may2017-bin.tgz

(in windows) untar the axiom binary
tar -zxf axiom-ubuntu64-may2017-bin.tgz

(in windows) set up the Windows X Server by installing 
<a href="https://sourceforge.net/projects/vcxsrv">VcXsrv</a>

(in windows) run VcXsrv and take all the defaults

(in ubuntu) install gcc
sudo apt-get install gcc

(in ubuntu) cd to the ubuntu subdirectory
cd /mnt/c/..../axiom/mnt/ubuntu
(note: ubuntu can read windows files using /mnt/c/..... to access the C: drive)

set up the shell variables
export AXIOM=`pwd`
export PATH=$AXIOM/bin:$PATH
export DISPLAY=localhost:0.0

run axiom
axiom


Note that you can add the AXIOM, PATH, and DISPLAY variables to your
.profile file so they are always available.

